dcterms:creator: M. Zavershynskyi
A. Skidanov
I. Polosukhin
dcterms:description: The NAPS dataset aims to build a large library of 'competitive programming' solutions to provide a basis of 'algorithmic problems'. It consists of small programs limited in scope, designed to do a single task, allowing models to learn complex fundamentals of algorithmic thinking.
dcterms:title: Natural Program Synthesis Dataset (NAPS)

dcterms:creator: U. Alon
M. Zilberstein
O. Levy
E. Yahav
dcterms:description: The dataset consists of Java open source code from 11 popular projects on GitHub, providing a large and diverse corpus of real source code. It is used to analyze methods extracted from these projects for program synthesis tasks.
dcterms:title: Java open source code
